This paper deals with the problem of colouring point visibility graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves algorithms and complexity analysis, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also discusses graph theory concepts such as chromatic number and clique number, which could place it under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Graph Theory).
